banks. The easiest way for students is here. Discover now!","name":"Opening a Bank Account in Turkiye: A Guide for Students","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-bank-account-opening/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-bank-account-opening/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/opening-a-bank-account-for-international-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-bank-account-opening/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the things I thought when I first came to Turkey was: &#8220;Are all payments here made in cash?&#8221; The answer is very clear: No. If you are a university student in Turkey, especially if you are a foreign national, having a bank account is almost a necessity. It both makes your life easier and formalizes things.</p>


