<p class="wp-block-paragraph">More flexible but generally more expensive. Some companies offer packages for <strong>$150-$250</strong> per year. Compared to SSI, it has advantages such as faster appointments and private hospital privileges. However, you should read your policy carefully because some chronic diseases or psychological support may not be covered.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8220;If you want to examine how the SSI system works from official sources, you can take a look at <a href="https://sgd.sgk.gov.tr/Home/Index2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the information page on the SSI&#8217;s own website</a>.&#8221;</p>
</blockquote>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2025-student-insurance-fees-and-what-they-cover">2025 Student Insurance Fees and What They Cover</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Figures change frequently due to the exchange rate, but the general outlook for 2025 is as follows:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sgk-and-private-insurance-fees-comparison">SGK and Private Insurance Fees Comparison</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Insurance Type</th>
<th>Average Annual Cost (USD)</th>
<th>Coverage</th>
<th>Benefits</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>SGK</td>
<td>$35 x 12 = <strong>$420</strong></td>
<td>State hospitals, some medicines</td>
<td>Affordable price, widespread access</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Private Insurance</td>
<td><strong>$150 &#8211; $250</strong></td>
<td>Private hospitals with contracts, basic treatment</td>
<td>Fast service, private clinics</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="excluded-health-services">Excluded Health Services</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some policies may not cover dental treatment, cosmetic surgery or maternity services. So read the contract twice before signing it.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="tabulated-sample-cost-calculation">Tabulated Sample Cost Calculation</h4>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
